All Implemented Interfaces:
ClementiniGeometry, Cloneable, Comparable, Externalizable, FeatureGeometry, Geometry, GeometryCollection, HitTest, MultiPoint, PointApplicatorUser, Serializable, Shape
Direct Known Subclasses:
FeaturePoint, PointM
public class Point
extends Point2D.Double
implements MultiPoint, Comparable, Externalizable

This class represents the Point type. For performance reasons, this class is not implemented as an interface as we do for other Geometry types like Polygon. This is because access to the X and Y member variables is much faster as compared with access using the corresponding get methods. This difference in access times become important as Point is used very frequently.
